 {"id":"br-r37-c1-lmviu","title":"parity: add_path/add_cycle/add_star keyword parameter names","description":"NetworkX exposes add_path(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_path, **attr), add_cycle(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_cycle, **attr), and add_star(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_star, **attr). FNX currently names these parameters G and nodes, so documented keyword calls like fnx.add_path(G_to_add_to=G, nodes_for_path=[1,2]) raise TypeError. Align the public signatures while preserving positional behavior and add parity tests.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T06:20:06.172080189Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T06:23:19.168859030Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T06:23:19.167009410Z","close_reason":"Completed in 92bae80","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-lz7u6","title":"parity: connectivity bridge_components missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.bridge_components(G) returns 2-edge-connected components after removing bridges. Not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrapper delegating to nx.algorithms.connectivity.bridge_components via _networkx_graph_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:44:53.163889437Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T12:57:50.253206642Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T12:57:50.251308058Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: bridge_components wrapper","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-m4msi","title":"parity: utils.random_sequence powerlaw_sequence + zipf_rv + cumulative_distribution + is_valid_tree_degree_sequence (4 functions)","description":"Four random-sequence utilities from networkx.utils.random_sequence not surfaced by franken_networkx: powerlaw_sequence(n, exponent=2.0, seed=None), zipf_rv(alpha, xmin=1, seed=None), cumulative_distribution(distribution), is_valid_tree_degree_sequence(degree_sequence). These are used by stochastic graph generators and degree-sequence sanity checks. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level and adding to __all__.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T21:59:39.857059179Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T21:59:39.857059179Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
